<detailed-description>
<section>
<heading lvl="1">DESCRIPTION OF THE NEW VARIETY </heading>
<paragraph id="P-0005" lvl="0"><number>&lsqb;0005&rsqb;</number> The new variety &lsquo;LLANOS HASS&rsquo; is vigorous, upright with a medium to large height. Anthocyanin is not present in the stems of young shoots. The leaflets are large, horizontal, long and narrow with blades folding concave with a lanceolate shape. The tips of the leaflets are acute and anthocyanin is present in newly emerged leaves. The following description is of plants grown in Kwinana, Hope Valley, Western Australia with color descriptions in accordance with the Color Chart of The Royal Horticultural Society, London (3<highlight><superscript>rd </superscript></highlight>ed. 1995). The plants described were grafted in 1996 onto rootstock as previously described. </paragraph>
<paragraph id="P-0006" lvl="0"><number>&lsqb;0006&rsqb;</number> All dimensions are in millimeters, weights in grams (unless otherwise stated).  
